1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:02,070
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:03,610
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,610 --> 00:00:05,080
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:13,150 --> 00:00:14,350
(Episode 34)

5
00:00:16,390 --> 00:00:18,720
The gems are real, aren't they?

6
00:00:23,230 --> 00:00:24,630
Out of the way. Let me through.

7
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:32,140
We are gathered here today...

8
00:00:32,470 --> 00:00:34,610
to confirm the authenticity
of the ornament...

9
00:00:35,140 --> 00:00:38,880
scheduled for exhibition
at the Adele Gallery.

10
00:00:41,050 --> 00:00:43,110
As an international gemologist,

11
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:47,790
I state that my evaluation is based
solely on objective facts.

12
00:00:51,220 --> 00:00:53,390
I will now share the results.

13
00:00:53,390 --> 00:00:54,960
No, wait. Hold on a second.

14
00:00:55,090 --> 00:00:56,360
The results are clear.

15
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:00,770
The gems in this ornament...

16
00:01:04,170 --> 00:01:06,570
are not genuine.

17
00:01:07,140 --> 00:01:08,170
Are they really fake?

18
00:01:08,170 --> 00:01:09,410
Are you sure about the appraisal?

19
00:01:09,470 --> 00:01:11,580
What does this mean for its status
as a cultural asset?

20
00:01:11,740 --> 00:01:14,410
- Are these results accurate?
- Are you sure?

21
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:16,710
Are you certain
about your appraisal?

22
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,350
Please comment.

23
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:21,150
Will the exhibition proceed
as planned?

24
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,820
Please give us a comment.

25
00:01:23,490 --> 00:01:24,620
Is this true?

26
00:01:26,290 --> 00:01:27,590
Please make a statement.

27
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:31,130
Are you absolutely certain
about the results?

28
00:01:31,430 --> 00:01:32,660
Please say something.

29
00:01:35,230 --> 00:01:39,470
What was that?
Why did you act on your own?

30
00:01:40,740 --> 00:01:44,780
I bet you were going to say
they were real until we showed up.

31
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:51,850
All you gave me
was this one appraisal report, sir.

32
00:01:54,620 --> 00:01:56,890
Then why bother
with a press conference?

33
00:01:57,020 --> 00:02:00,990
If my appraisal report went public,
people would come looking for me.

34
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:04,930
I would've eventually had to step up
and make the announcement myself.

35
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,670
Since a press conference
was inevitable,

36
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,330
I wanted to take the initiative...

37
00:02:09,330 --> 00:02:12,640
and make it clear
that I'm the one responsible...

38
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:14,040
for this appraisal.

39
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:15,570
What?

40
00:02:15,670 --> 00:02:16,840
The one responsible?

41
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:21,810
If anything were to go wrong,
it would all be my fault.

42
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:24,120
I wanted to make it clear...

43
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,750
so it wouldn't backfire
on the Adele Gallery,

44
00:02:27,020 --> 00:02:28,890
the Adele Group, or you.

45
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:31,220
She's lying through her teeth.

46
00:02:31,220 --> 00:02:32,220
Quiet!

47
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:36,060
Did you really do this...

48
00:02:36,060 --> 00:02:38,460
because you're willing
to take the responsibility?

49
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:42,630
Wasn't this whole situation
kind of a test?

50
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:45,170
It seemed you wanted to see...

51
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:47,710
if I could be of use to you,

52
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,040
so I showed you my resolve.

53
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:56,920
No, that's not it.
She must have an ulterior motive.

54
00:02:57,580 --> 00:02:59,220
You can't let her fool you.

55
00:03:11,260 --> 00:03:13,100
The gems in this ornament...

56
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:16,300
are not genuine.

57
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:21,640
I didn't see any issue
with the press conference.

58
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:26,180
Why did my mother think
something was wrong?

59
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:28,980
She said something strange
to me yesterday.

60
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:31,580
She asked me to look after
the bio vision...

61
00:03:31,580 --> 00:03:32,950
in case anything happened to her.

62
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:37,260
But I guess I was just
overthinking things.

63
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:39,120
I'm glad everything's okay.

64
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,340
Is there something else
you wanted to say?

65
00:03:52,670 --> 00:03:53,740
The wedding...

66
00:03:55,140 --> 00:03:56,710
Are you really
going through with it?

67
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:58,780
Yes.

68
00:04:00,510 --> 00:04:02,010
Do you love Hyun Jun?

69
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:07,250
In your eyes and your expression
when you look at Hyun Jun,

70
00:04:07,820 --> 00:04:11,090
I've never seen any love.

71
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:15,130
You only see what you want to see,
don't you?

72
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:20,600
First, you saw me as a dead woman,
and then as Chloe.

73
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:24,300
Don't you dare presume to know
what's in my heart.

74
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:27,540
Then give me a straight answer
right now.

75
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:29,770
Do you...

76
00:04:30,810 --> 00:04:32,040
love Hyun Jun?

77
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:56,430
I'm going to marry
Director Park Hyun Jun.

78
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:59,640
We're about to become family,

79
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,570
so I'd appreciate
your congratulations.

80
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,980
Save the congratulations.

81
00:05:05,710 --> 00:05:07,110
Instead,
you'd better watch yourself.

82
00:05:10,580 --> 00:05:12,780
From now on, the only person
who can hold Chloe's hand...

83
00:05:15,090 --> 00:05:16,190
is me.

84
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,200
Let's go.

85
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:37,980
She can't even say she loves him.

86
00:06:00,470 --> 00:06:02,000
What on earth are you thinking?

87
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:06,670
You're marrying me, so what are you
pulling with Min Jun?

88
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:09,440
I had to talk to him
about President Kim.

89
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,840
What kind of conversation...

90
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:14,950
involves him holding your wrist?

91
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:18,050
Don't be so childish.

92
00:06:20,490 --> 00:06:21,490
Is that...

93
00:06:22,690 --> 00:06:24,260
all you see?

94
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:28,160
Can't you see
my childish behavior...

95
00:06:29,190 --> 00:06:31,130
comes from being afraid
of losing you?

96
00:06:32,330 --> 00:06:34,700
You couldn't even say you love me
in front of him.

97
00:06:34,970 --> 00:06:38,040
What about my pride?
It hit rock bottom because of that!

98
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:42,010
Can't you see
how pathetic I'm being,

99
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,510
even bringing this up?

100
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:49,610
Can't you see that?

101
00:07:00,630 --> 00:07:03,130
You may not love me, but I...

102
00:07:08,070 --> 00:07:09,070
I love you.

103
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:14,840
So...

104
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:19,840
Just lie for me
every once in a while.

105
00:07:23,150 --> 00:07:25,350
If someone asks
whether you love me, just...

106
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:30,250
Just say you do,
or at least nod your head.

107
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:35,160
If I get any more childish
and pathetic,

108
00:07:36,490 --> 00:07:38,230
I don't think I can stand it.

109
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:43,330
I thought you would be easy.

110
00:07:44,670 --> 00:07:47,870
I thought that even if I used you
and threw you away,

111
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:51,910
you'd just act like it was nothing.

112
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:09,830
I heard you loud and clear.

113
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:13,160
I'll be more careful from now on.

114
00:08:40,990 --> 00:08:42,690
Yes, Assemblyman Kwon.

115
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:45,100
Did you see the press conference?

116
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:51,400
Now that the gems
have been confirmed as fake,

117
00:08:51,870 --> 00:08:53,340
we have our justification.

118
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,270
Without another appraisal,

119
00:08:55,610 --> 00:08:58,210
its designation as a cultural asset
will be revoked.

120
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:02,710
Yes, I've already arranged for it.

121
00:09:03,810 --> 00:09:07,420
Just send it overseas
and keep it hidden.

122
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:10,620
Once people start
to forget about it,

123
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:14,360
you can quietly sell it.

124
00:09:17,730 --> 00:09:18,730
Now,

125
00:09:19,930 --> 00:09:23,700
is my request moving forward too?

126
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:35,950
I can't believe you.

127
00:09:36,050 --> 00:09:37,110
How could you...

128
00:09:37,110 --> 00:09:39,320
hold a press conference
without talking to me first?

129
00:09:39,550 --> 00:09:42,520
If I'd asked you,
you would've tried to stop me.

130
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,760
Is this the file you got
from Mrs. Han?

131
00:09:47,990 --> 00:09:50,430
Yes, it's what you asked for
the other day.

132
00:09:52,830 --> 00:09:56,430
I'm sorry,
but may I ask for one more favor?

133
00:09:56,630 --> 00:09:57,640
Park Tae Ho.

134
00:09:58,540 --> 00:10:01,110
Please look into Chairman Park
of the Adele Group.

135
00:10:03,910 --> 00:10:05,440
I'm telling you,
Ihwachae is the real deal.

136
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:07,710
They know everything
about the key players...

137
00:10:07,710 --> 00:10:09,080
in politics and business.

138
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,980
They gathered all this information
on Chairman Park so quickly.

139
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,090
It also includes information
on Assemblyman Kwon,

140
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:15,850
the owner of that ornament.

141
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:18,190
(Mineral Rights
and National Bond Funding)

142
00:10:20,690 --> 00:10:23,760
Chairman Park doesn't seem satisfied
with Adele Group as it is.

143
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:25,900
He's trying to expand overseas...

144
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:28,570
and control key mineral resources.

145
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:31,400
This isn't just
a business expansion.

146
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:37,070
He's trying to control key resources
to expand Adele's influence.

147
00:10:37,710 --> 00:10:41,280
That way, not just the government,
but other corporations too,

148
00:10:41,650 --> 00:10:44,020
will be unable to ignore
Chairman Park's demands.

149
00:10:45,180 --> 00:10:47,150
He already lives like a king
at Adele.

150
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:50,390
Does he want to reign like one
outside of it too?

151
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:56,060
His greed for money is evolving
into a desire...

152
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:58,460
for power.

153
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:06,340
Mr. Kwon, you have special ties...

154
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:10,140
with foreign government officials,
don't you?

155
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:13,780
As for the lobbying funds needed,
I'll prepare them.

156
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:16,710
All you have to do is make
the delivery.

157
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:18,950
Once we secure
the exclusive development rights,

158
00:11:19,980 --> 00:11:24,060
I will be sure to send you
that gift you wanted.

159
00:11:24,990 --> 00:11:26,090
What?

160
00:11:30,930 --> 00:11:32,300
Yes, of course.

161
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:34,670
I'm counting on you,
Assemblyman Kwon.

162
00:11:35,870 --> 00:11:36,870
Sure.

163
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:43,170
Since when were you so trusting?

164
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:46,140
If you're going to be snide, leave.

165
00:11:46,140 --> 00:11:47,980
I'm not being snide. I'm concerned.

166
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:50,880
I worry that trusting Kim Myung Hui
will blow this important deal.

167
00:11:50,950 --> 00:11:53,050
Or maybe you're falling apart
because you're afraid...

168
00:11:53,050 --> 00:11:54,950
she'll take the gallery from you.

169
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:57,220
I can't believe you. Darn it!

170
00:11:59,590 --> 00:12:02,030
Fine, have it your way.

171
00:12:02,330 --> 00:12:04,060
If it blows up in your face,

172
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:06,100
don't say I didn't warn you.

173
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,160
Darn you.

174
00:12:11,470 --> 00:12:12,870
Honestly.

175
00:12:13,370 --> 00:12:16,410
What? Kim Myung Hui is going
to ruin my plans?

176
00:12:16,510 --> 00:12:18,040
She'll go down first,

177
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:20,310
especially after
that press conference.

178
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:23,650
Driven by her grudge
against Jung Ran,

179
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:26,250
she's promising
to be completely loyal to me.

180
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,290
I just need to tame her...

181
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:32,190
and put her to good use.

182
00:12:33,090 --> 00:12:34,090
Right?

183
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,030
(BIT Life, President Kim Myung Hui)

184
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:45,270
If this deal goes through,
Chairman Park gains even more power.

185
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:49,840
His crimes will never see the light,
and he'll be completely untouchable.

186
00:12:51,940 --> 00:12:53,110
But...

187
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,410
if the ornament's owner...

188
00:12:55,410 --> 00:12:57,210
and Chairman Park
turn against each other,

189
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:01,890
will this deal and his ambitions...

190
00:13:02,350 --> 00:13:03,920
go up in smoke?

191
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:07,360
What's going on
in that head of yours?

192
00:13:08,090 --> 00:13:09,490
You held a press conference alone,

193
00:13:09,490 --> 00:13:11,300
and you're planning
without me again?

194
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:12,730
I'm just trying...

195
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:15,530
to get a clear picture
of the situation.

196
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,800
To take down Chairman Park,

197
00:13:18,470 --> 00:13:20,970
I openly lied about a gem appraisal.

198
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:23,970
I can't let my actions end up
giving him more power.

199
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,280
How should I...

200
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:31,350
go about sabotaging this deal?

201
00:13:46,730 --> 00:13:47,900
Where have you been?

202
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:51,100
I was just talking
to Director Park Hyun Jun.

203
00:13:51,740 --> 00:13:53,640
Are you busy
with your wedding plans?

204
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:57,140
I thought I was clear
that my wedding comes first.

205
00:13:58,340 --> 00:14:01,580
Right. I sacrificed my own marriage
for this opportunity.

206
00:14:01,650 --> 00:14:03,110
I have to make it count.

207
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:08,790
Choi Yu Na...
What's the best way to use you?

208
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:12,690
I know you're feeling impatient,

209
00:14:13,190 --> 00:14:14,990
but you need to see the problem
for what it is.

210
00:14:15,730 --> 00:14:18,300
Why do you think
your wedding is hitting a wall?

211
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:23,030
Do you even know
what your biggest obstacle is?

212
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:27,340
It's because
President Kim and Park Min Jun...

213
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,610
are so against it...

214
00:14:28,610 --> 00:14:31,380
You still don't get it, do you?

215
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,580
Get what?

216
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:36,010
The biggest obstacle
to your marriage...

217
00:14:36,450 --> 00:14:37,920
is Chairman Park Tae Ho.

218
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,120
What?

219
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:43,790
He's giving President Kim
and Park Min Jun free rein.

220
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:48,830
Do you really think
he can't control those two?

221
00:14:49,590 --> 00:14:53,760
It's not that he can't.
It's that he won't.

222
00:14:56,870 --> 00:14:59,200
If you can't get him to move,

223
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:02,110
this wedding is never going
to happen.

224
00:15:03,540 --> 00:15:05,810
Then how am I supposed
to pressure him?

225
00:15:05,810 --> 00:15:08,610
I still can't,
even with what I have on him.

226
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:13,220
We need more leverage
on Park Tae Ho.

227
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:17,790
Since one isn't enough,
we'll need more.

228
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:23,490
He seemed to be up to something
at the gallery today.

229
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:26,330
He even had President Kim Myung Hui
involved.

230
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,730
At the gallery?

231
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:32,670
If he was involved
in something illegal,

232
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:35,640
you could use that as leverage,
don't you think?

233
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:37,680
Look into it.

234
00:15:38,140 --> 00:15:41,950
I'll help you figure out
how to use whatever you find.

235
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:47,580
Go on, dig up some dirt
and bring it to me.

236
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:50,850
If you get caught
and have a clash with Chairman Park,

237
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:51,890
even better.

238
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:01,670
Chloe.

239
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:05,600
She's a piece of work,
but she's not wrong.

240
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:09,070
No one but the chairman
can control...

241
00:16:09,270 --> 00:16:10,940
President Kim and Min Jun.

242
00:16:12,940 --> 00:16:15,910
Besides, if I want to go up
against the chairman,

243
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,380
I need more leverage.

244
00:16:24,820 --> 00:16:26,560
(Royal Gift Ornament Declared Fake)

245
00:16:26,620 --> 00:16:28,460
(Will Its Cultural Status
Be Revoked?)

246
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:32,360
On top of that,

247
00:16:32,730 --> 00:16:34,930
even President Kim Myung Hui
is involved.

248
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:40,000
This means
I'd have leverage against her too,

249
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:43,140
so I have to find out
no matter what.

250
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:47,680
But how?

251
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:55,690
Mom, Dad!

252
00:16:56,020 --> 00:16:57,190
- I'm up.
- Dad, wake up.

253
00:16:57,190 --> 00:16:58,620
- What is it?
- What's wrong?

254
00:16:58,620 --> 00:16:59,920
Are you busy tomorrow?

255
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:03,490
Even if you are, come with me
to the chairman's house.

256
00:17:04,660 --> 00:17:07,300
- Why would we go there?
- Forget it.

257
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:10,100
I want nothing to do
with the Adele family.

258
00:17:10,570 --> 00:17:12,170
You don't want me to get married?

259
00:17:13,070 --> 00:17:15,540
I don't want to get tangled up
with that family.

260
00:17:15,610 --> 00:17:16,870
Exactly.

261
00:17:16,940 --> 00:17:19,540
Of all families,
why does it have to be them?

262
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:21,850
We're basically
their mortal enemies now.

263
00:17:22,950 --> 00:17:25,750
Have you forgotten
how powerful Adele Group is?

264
00:17:25,820 --> 00:17:28,790
Do you think it's easy to marry
into a conglomerate family?

265
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:32,990
I have to marry
into a wealthy family...

266
00:17:33,060 --> 00:17:35,490
to support you in your old age.

267
00:17:35,860 --> 00:17:36,860
In our old age?

268
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:41,700
Now that you mention it,
that is a concern.

269
00:17:42,670 --> 00:17:46,100
Right. Then tell us.

270
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,510
Why are we going there tomorrow?

271
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:52,180
Are we meeting
to discuss your wedding again?

272
00:17:57,280 --> 00:17:59,380
Tomorrow,
instead of just dinner,

273
00:17:59,380 --> 00:18:01,020
we'll be checking out
my future home.

274
00:18:01,590 --> 00:18:03,920
All you have to do is do
what I tell you to.

275
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:08,330
- You can do that, right?
- Check where you're going to live?

276
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:27,110
It came from Assemblyman Kwon.

277
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:29,280
It outlines the demands
of overseas parties...

278
00:18:29,510 --> 00:18:32,780
in exchange for granting you
exclusive development rights.

279
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:35,550
How blatant.

280
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:38,890
They're practically begging me
for money.

281
00:18:39,490 --> 00:18:42,230
But still,
once I get these exclusive rights,

282
00:18:42,690 --> 00:18:44,860
that in itself becomes power.

283
00:18:46,330 --> 00:18:48,470
The government
and other corporations...

284
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:52,640
will all have to tread carefully
and bow before me.

285
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:55,910
Adele will become
a global corporation,

286
00:18:57,510 --> 00:19:01,850
and my power will be untouchable.

287
00:19:20,030 --> 00:19:21,930
What are your plans for the gallery?

288
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:24,300
It's becoming too much for me
to manage on my own.

289
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,770
Should I give it back to Jung Ran,

290
00:19:28,940 --> 00:19:31,810
or should I let Myung Hui manage it?

291
00:19:48,660 --> 00:19:51,060
I'm sorry about the other day.

292
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:55,130
It's okay.

293
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:57,400
I understand completely.

294
00:20:00,370 --> 00:20:02,240
Is that why you stopped by?

295
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:07,180
Did you really ask Chloe
to manage the bio division?

296
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:10,580
I'm working on gem appraisals...

297
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:12,680
and am interested
in running the gallery.

298
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:16,420
I asked her to step in
in case I get too busy.

299
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:19,990
Are you sure everything's okay?

300
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:23,960
Of course. I'm fine.

301
00:20:24,860 --> 00:20:27,560
Even if something were to happen,

302
00:20:27,630 --> 00:20:29,670
I'll find a way to take care of it.

303
00:20:30,100 --> 00:20:32,700
You just stay focused
and hold your ground.

304
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:34,240
Got it?

305
00:20:35,170 --> 00:20:38,510
If anything happens,
please let me know.

306
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:40,610
Don't try to handle it all
by yourself.

307
00:20:45,350 --> 00:20:46,550
My dear son.

308
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:49,620
Looks like I don't have to worry
about you anymore.

309
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,830
The chairman is asking for you.

310
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:03,230
It seems like you're going
to the gallery together.

311
00:21:15,950 --> 00:21:18,380
This gallery is my domain.

312
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:23,750
Fire me if you want,
but you can't place her here.

313
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:29,890
If you won't give it back to me,
then find somebody else.

314
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:36,800
Everything in the Adele Group,
including this gallery, is mine.

315
00:21:38,140 --> 00:21:42,840
That includes deciding
who's in charge here. Understood?

316
00:21:43,810 --> 00:21:44,840
As of today,

317
00:21:45,780 --> 00:21:47,710
the new director
of the Adele Gallery...

318
00:21:49,410 --> 00:21:50,410
is Kim Myung Hui.

319
00:21:51,150 --> 00:21:52,150
Honey!

320
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:54,950
Thank you, sir.

321
00:21:56,620 --> 00:21:58,620
Is this really
how you're going to play it?

322
00:21:59,790 --> 00:22:01,560
Fine. The gloves are off.

323
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:05,300
Do you have any idea
why that tramp changed her tune?

324
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:08,570
I...

325
00:22:11,770 --> 00:22:13,540
- I...
- Jung Ran!

326
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:16,440
Ms. Kim.

327
00:22:20,980 --> 00:22:21,980
Police.

328
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,680
You're under arrest
for issuing a fraudulent appraisal...

329
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:26,020
that obstructed business operations.

330
00:22:26,650 --> 00:22:29,250
Wait, what? An arrest?

331
00:22:30,050 --> 00:22:32,920
You have the right to remain silent
and to have an attorney.

332
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:36,930
- Cuff her.
- What? Wait a minute.

333
00:22:37,460 --> 00:22:39,130
What do you think you're doing?

334
00:22:39,730 --> 00:22:42,970
How dare you cuff one of my people
right in front of me?

335
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,200
Back off,

336
00:22:45,140 --> 00:22:46,370
or I'll charge you with obstruction.

337
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:49,110
- Step aside.
- What?

338
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:50,640
No, wait.

339
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:52,980
I'll be all right.

340
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:54,980
Please don't worry about me.

341
00:22:55,810 --> 00:22:57,410
- But...
- Take her away.

342
00:22:58,050 --> 00:22:59,420
Wait a minute.

343
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:01,950
Hey! Which precinct are you from?

344
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:03,390
Why you...

345
00:23:04,390 --> 00:23:07,090
Manager Kang!

346
00:23:13,930 --> 00:23:16,200
What brings you here unexpectedly?

347
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,940
I'm here to work
on the wedding plans.

348
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,610
The chairman said
the wedding's back on.

349
00:23:22,210 --> 00:23:23,210
I'm sure you heard.

350
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:27,580
There was quite a commotion at home,
so I'm aware.

351
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:30,710
However, I wasn't told
you'd be visiting.

352
00:23:31,820 --> 00:23:33,480
This will be my home
once I'm married,

353
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:35,550
so I won't be calling
every time I come over.

354
00:23:37,020 --> 00:23:39,520
I need to check on the room
for things to buy,

355
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:40,960
so know that.

356
00:23:44,090 --> 00:23:46,360
We'll look around then.

357
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:48,630
Min Jun's room is
on the second floor, right?

358
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:50,530
Just a moment.

359
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:53,300
I can't let you into his room...

360
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:55,270
without permission
while he's not here.

361
00:23:55,940 --> 00:23:57,540
I'd get in trouble
if I let you in...

362
00:23:57,810 --> 00:23:59,880
and something went missing.

363
00:24:00,510 --> 00:24:03,750
What? Who are you calling a thief?

364
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:08,050
Well, your daughter
was thrown out of here...

365
00:24:08,250 --> 00:24:10,150
once before for stealing.

366
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:15,830
Fine. If you're that worried,
you can come up and watch us.

367
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,860
Exactly. You can come up with us.

368
00:24:18,130 --> 00:24:19,930
- That settles it.
- Exactly.

369
00:24:19,930 --> 00:24:22,630
Goodness me.
I get it. Please stop pushing.

370
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:25,940
Gosh, I left my phone in the car.

371
00:24:26,270 --> 00:24:28,170
- You guys go on ahead.
- Sure thing.

372
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:29,700
What's this?

373
00:25:30,170 --> 00:25:31,940
It looks thick,
but why is it so light?

374
00:25:47,620 --> 00:25:49,090
(World Gemological Institute)

375
00:25:49,150 --> 00:25:51,350
(AD Appraisals:
Gemstone Appraisal Report)

376
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:53,320
This is...

377
00:25:55,130 --> 00:25:56,930
An exclusive overseas
mining development right?

378
00:26:00,430 --> 00:26:01,500
Members of Congress...

379
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:05,000
and even foreign officials.
This is a list of payoffs.

380
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:13,240
And what's this?
A certificate of authenticity?

381
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:14,810
Mrs. Ok.

382
00:26:15,950 --> 00:26:17,110
Mrs. Ok!

383
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:35,870
Mrs. Ok!

384
00:26:37,370 --> 00:26:38,370
Mrs...

385
00:26:40,370 --> 00:26:41,500
What is this?

386
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,710
Why are you all coming down
from upstairs?

387
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:47,180
Ms. Choi brought her parents...

388
00:26:47,980 --> 00:26:49,910
Where exactly is that piece of work?

389
00:26:52,780 --> 00:26:53,820
Hello.

390
00:26:57,150 --> 00:26:59,460
What were you doing in there?

391
00:27:01,420 --> 00:27:02,730
I just needed to grab a pen.

392
00:27:04,490 --> 00:27:07,300
Whatever.
My head's spinning, so get out.

393
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,830
Get them all out of my sight.

394
00:27:10,270 --> 00:27:12,340
- How dare you talk to us like...
- Why you...

395
00:27:12,340 --> 00:27:14,470
I hope you'll excuse her.

396
00:27:15,110 --> 00:27:18,810
She just saw President Kim
get arrested,

397
00:27:18,810 --> 00:27:20,680
so she's a bit shaken.

398
00:27:21,380 --> 00:27:23,650
President Kim was arrested?

399
00:27:24,410 --> 00:27:25,780
On what charges?

400
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:29,450
What in the world
are you talking about?

401
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:31,490
Is Ms. Kim going to be okay?

402
00:27:31,490 --> 00:27:33,160
Shut it.

403
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:37,690
Why are you just standing there?
Get them out of my sight.

404
00:27:38,190 --> 00:27:39,500
I said, get out!

405
00:27:39,500 --> 00:27:40,960
- What the...
- You witch.

406
00:27:41,030 --> 00:27:43,630
But ma'am,

407
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:46,570
shouldn't you be in the annex
instead of here?

408
00:27:47,840 --> 00:27:49,740
- Hey!
- Oh, my.

409
00:27:52,780 --> 00:27:53,780
Oh, dear.

410
00:27:54,910 --> 00:27:56,380
- Maybe next time.
- Get them out of here.

411
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:57,910
I have terrible news!

412
00:27:58,420 --> 00:28:01,820
President Kim Myung Hui was arrested
by the police.

413
00:28:02,250 --> 00:28:04,620
The president? Why all of a sudden?

414
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:07,160
Tell me exactly what happened.

415
00:28:07,290 --> 00:28:10,490
Remember that press conference
she held at the gallery?

416
00:28:11,530 --> 00:28:14,230
She lied in the appraisal report.

417
00:28:15,230 --> 00:28:17,730
She claimed
that the real gems were fake.

418
00:28:18,540 --> 00:28:21,440
That alone shouldn't be grounds
for a sudden arrest.

419
00:28:23,740 --> 00:28:26,810
I'm sure the police
had a good reason.

420
00:28:29,810 --> 00:28:31,050
Choi Yu Na.

421
00:28:31,210 --> 00:28:33,580
Did you find something
like I told you to?

422
00:28:41,390 --> 00:28:42,590
What are you talking about?

423
00:28:43,290 --> 00:28:44,460
President Kim's...

424
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:47,430
been arrested.

425
00:28:47,700 --> 00:28:48,730
What do you mean?

426
00:28:50,070 --> 00:28:51,500
Explain everything to me.

427
00:28:53,870 --> 00:28:57,010
Can you check with the legal team
and find out what's going on?

428
00:28:57,740 --> 00:28:59,240
- Sure.
- Got it.

429
00:29:05,950 --> 00:29:08,380
You know something, don't you?

430
00:29:10,020 --> 00:29:12,760
I dug for dirt on Chairman Park
like you said,

431
00:29:13,820 --> 00:29:14,860
and I found something.

432
00:29:15,690 --> 00:29:19,030
I can't help you
if you don't share what you know.

433
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:28,370
There's a hidden reason
behind the false appraisal.

434
00:29:29,470 --> 00:29:30,470
A hidden reason?

435
00:29:36,010 --> 00:29:37,850
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

436
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:41,280
Get the legal team on it
and bail out Myung Hui now.

437
00:29:41,750 --> 00:29:44,920
Have the PR team kill any articles,
no matter what.

438
00:29:45,690 --> 00:29:47,320
Give Assemblyman Kwon cash
if you have to,

439
00:29:47,390 --> 00:29:49,290
to make sure
he doesn't change his mind!

440
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:50,560
Yes, sir.

441
00:29:55,870 --> 00:29:57,070
Sir!

442
00:29:58,330 --> 00:29:59,670
What on earth have you done?

443
00:30:01,500 --> 00:30:03,670
What did you threaten
my mother with?

444
00:30:05,710 --> 00:30:07,510
Threaten her?

445
00:30:08,080 --> 00:30:11,050
My mother would never appraise
a genuine gem as a fake.

446
00:30:11,050 --> 00:30:13,150
She would never make
a mistake like that.

447
00:30:14,420 --> 00:30:16,750
Did you force her to give
a false appraisal?

448
00:30:17,590 --> 00:30:20,120
What did you drag her into?

449
00:30:31,900 --> 00:30:32,900
Ms. Kim.

450
00:30:39,340 --> 00:30:40,410
An anonymous tip claims...

451
00:30:43,510 --> 00:30:44,950
you held a press conference...

452
00:30:45,620 --> 00:30:47,020
using a fraudulent appraisal report.

453
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:49,220
Do you admit to the allegation?

454
00:30:53,090 --> 00:30:55,960
Are you sure the tip was anonymous?

455
00:30:57,230 --> 00:31:00,830
Can't you tell me who the source is?

456
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,060
(Pearl in Red)

457
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:37,470
My mother isn't someone
who makes mistakes.

458
00:31:37,530 --> 00:31:39,940
Even now,
she's still protecting you.

459
00:31:40,140 --> 00:31:43,310
How much more are you going
to put my mother through?

460
00:31:43,570 --> 00:31:46,110
The tip came from you, didn't it?

461
00:31:46,110 --> 00:31:48,040
You seem to have the wrong idea.

462
00:31:48,140 --> 00:31:50,310
I don't care if you deny it.

463
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:55,150
I just want it to look
like someone else gave the tip.

464
00:31:55,450 --> 00:31:57,920
Wait. Come to think of it,
something odd happened.

465
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:58,920
Something odd?

466
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,690
Ms. Choi was at the house.

467
00:32:00,690 --> 00:32:02,190
She walked out of your study...

468
00:32:02,190 --> 00:32:03,690
right after Kim Myung Hui
got arrested.

469
00:32:03,860 --> 00:32:06,160
Get Ms. Choi in here right now!

470
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:09,370
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
